options.content:
# Amazon Redshift Identities and Objects

This dashboard shows identites and database objects in Amazon Redshift. 

Access control to database objects are defined by combination of identity, object and privilege. 

- Identity: User, Role, Group
- Object: Database, Schema, Table/View, Column, Function, Procedure, Language, Datashare, ML Model
- Privilege: CREATE, SELECT, ALTER, DROP, DELETE, INSERT, ... (depends on the object)

Visit **Amazon Redshift Privileges** dashboard to show privileges in Amazon Redshift.

targets.rawSQL: select count(*) from pg_user;
select count(*) from svv_roles;
select count(*) from pg_group;

panels.description: Switch Data Source to change current database.

targets.rawSQL: select current_database();

panels.title: Current Database

panels.description: Number or local schemas in current database.

targets.rawSQL:
select count(*) from svv_all_schemas
where schema_type = 'local'
and database_name = current_database()
;

panels.title: Local Schema

panels.description: Number or external schemas in current database

targets.rawSQL:
select count(*) from svv_all_schemas
where schema_type = 'external'
and database_name = current_database()
;

panels.title: Extrenal Schema

panels.description: Number or  local tables in current database. System tables are not included.

targets.rawSQL:
select count(*) from SVV_ALL_TABLES
where table_type = 'TABLE'
and schema_name not in ('pg_catalog', 'information_schema')
and database_name = current_database()
;

panels.title: Local Table

panels.description: Number or external tables in current database.

targets.rawSQL:
select count(*) from SVV_ALL_TABLES
where table_type = 'EXTERNAL TABLE'
and schema_name not in ('pg_catalog', 'information_schema')
and database_name = current_database()
;

panels.title: External Table

panels.description: Number or views in current database. System views are not included.

targets.rawSQL:
select count(*) from SVV_ALL_TABLES
where table_type = 'VIEW'
and schema_name not in ('pg_catalog', 'information_schema')
and database_name = current_database()
;

panels.title: View

panels.description: Number or functions in current database.

targets.rawSQL:
select count(*) from SVV_REDSHIFT_FUNCTIONS
where schema_name not in ('pg_catalog', 'information_schema')
and function_type in ('REGULAR FUNCTION', 'AGGREGATE FUNCTION', 'AGGREGATED FUNCTION')
and database_name = current_database()
;

panels.title: Function

panels.description: Number or procedures in current database.

targets.rawSQL:
select count(*) from SVV_REDSHIFT_FUNCTIONS
where schema_name not in ('pg_catalog', 'information_schema')
and function_type = 'STORED PROCEDURE'
and database_name = current_database()
;

panels.title: Procedure

panels.description: Number or ML Models in current database.

options.content:
# User, Role, Group

Lists of all user, role, group in the data source. 

- To administrate users, use
[CREATE USER](https://docs.aws.amazon.com/redshift/latest/dg/r_CREATE_USER.html),
[ALTER USER](https://docs.aws.amazon.com/redshift/latest/dg/r_ALTER_USER.html),
[DROP USER](https://docs.aws.amazon.com/redshift/latest/dg/r_DROP_USER.html).

- To administrate roles, use
[CREATE ROLE](https://docs.aws.amazon.com/redshift/latest/dg/r_CREATE_ROLE.html), 
[ALTER ROLE](https://docs.aws.amazon.com/redshift/latest/dg/r_ALTER_ROLE.html), 
[DROP ROLE](https://docs.aws.amazon.com/redshift/latest/dg/r_DROP_ROLE.html).

- To administrate groups, use
[CREATE GROUP](https://docs.aws.amazon.com/redshift/latest/dg/r_CREATE_GROUP.html), 
[ALTER GROUP](https://docs.aws.amazon.com/redshift/latest/dg/r_ALTER_GROUP.html), 
[DROP GROUP](https://docs.aws.amazon.com/redshift/latest/dg/r_DROP_GROUP.html).

panels.description: List of database users. num_group_assigned, num_roles_granted are the number of groups/roles assigned to each users.

targets.rawSQL:
select
  t1.usename, 
  t1.usecreatedb, 
  t1.usesuper, 
  t1.usecatupd,
  nvl(t2.num_groups_assigned, 0) as num_groups_assigned,
  nvl(t3.num_roles_granted, 0) as num_roles_granted
from pg_user t1
-- # of assigned groups
left join (
  select pg_user.usesysid, count(*) as num_groups_assigned
  from pg_user, pg_group
  where pg_user.usesysid = ANY(pg_group.grolist)
  group by pg_user.usesysid
  ) t2
on t1.usesysid = t2.usesysid
-- # of assigned roles
left join (
  select pg_user.usesysid, count(*) as num_roles_granted
  from pg_user
  where pg_user.usesysid in (select user_id from svv_user_grants)
  group by pg_user.usesysid
  ) t3
on t1.usesysid = t3.usesysid
;

select
  usename, 
  usecreatedb,
  usesuper,
  usecatupd,
  useconnlimit,
  syslogaccess,
  sessiontimeout,
  external_id
from SVL_USER_INFO
where usename not like 'f346c9b8%'  -- ignore internal user
;

panels.title: User

panels.description:
List of roles. num_roles_granted, num_users_granted are the number of roles/users assigned to each roles. 
external_id is the unique identifier of the role in the third-party identity provider.

targets.rawSQL:
select 
  t1.role_name, 
  t1.role_owner, 
  nvl(t2.num_roles_granted, 0) as num_roles_granted,
  nvl(t3.num_users_granted, 0) as num_users_granted,
  t1.external_id
from svv_roles t1
left join (
  select role_id, count(*) as num_roles_granted
  from svv_role_grants
  group by role_id
  ) t2
on t1.role_id = t2.role_id
left join (
  select role_id, count(*) as num_users_granted
  from svv_user_grants
  group by role_id
  ) t3
on t1.role_id = t3.role_id
order by role_name
;

panels.title: Role

panels.description: List of groups. num_user_assigned is the number of users assigned to each groups.

targets.rawSQL:
select
  t1.groname as group,
  nvl(t2.num_user_assigned, 0) as num_user_assigned
from pg_group t1
left join (
  select 
	pg_group.grosysid,
	count(*) as num_user_assigned
  from pg_group, pg_user
  where pg_user.usesysid = ANY(pg_group.grolist) 
  group by pg_group.grosysid
  ) t2
on t1.grosysid = t2.grosysid
order by groname
;

panels.title: Group

panels.description: List of role granted to user. admin_option is a value that indicates whether the user can grant the role to other users and roles.

targets.rawSQL:
select
  trim(role_name) as role_name, 
  user_name, 
  admin_option
from svv_user_grants
order by role_name, user_name
;

panels.title: Role assigned to User

panels.description: List of role assigned to role.

targets.rawSQL:
select 
  trim(granted_role_name) as granted_role_name,
  role_name
from svv_role_grants
order by granted_role_name, role_name
;

panels.title: Role assigned to Role

panels.description: List of users in each group

targets.rawSQL:
SELECT 
	t1.groname as group,
	t2.usename
FROM pg_group t1, pg_user t2
WHERE t2.usesysid = ANY(t1.grolist) 
ORDER BY 1, 2
;

panels.title: Group assigned to User

panels.description: User not assigned to role, role not assigned to role is not shown in this panel.

targets.rawSQL:
select
  t1.role_id::varchar as id, 
  t1.role_name::varchar || ' (role)' as title
from svv_roles t1
where t1.role_id in (
  select role_id from svv_role_grants
  union all
  select granted_role_id from svv_role_grants
  )
union all
select
  user_id::varchar as id, 
  user_name::varchar || ' (user)'as title
from svv_user_grants
;

select
  role_id::varchar as target, 
  granted_role_id::varchar as source,
  role_id::varchar || '_' ||granted_role_id::varchar as id
from svv_role_grants
union all
select 
  user_id::varchar as target, 
  role_id::varchar as source, 
  user_id::varchar || '_' || role_id::varchar as id
from svv_user_grants
;

panels.title: Role assigned to Role, User

panels.description: User not assigned to group, group not assigned with user is not shown in this panel.

targets.rawSQL:
select
  t1.grosysid::int as id,
  t1.groname::varchar || ' (group)' as title
from pg_group t1
left join (
  select 
	pg_group.grosysid,
	count(*) as num_user_assigned
  from pg_group, pg_user
  where pg_user.usesysid = ANY(pg_group.grolist) 
  group by pg_group.grosysid
  ) t2
on t1.grosysid = t2.grosysid
where t2.num_user_assigned > 0

union all

select
  usesysid as id, 
  usename::varchar || ' (user)' as title
from pg_user, pg_group
WHERE pg_user.usesysid = ANY(pg_group.grolist) 
;

SELECT 
  pg_user.usesysid as target,
	pg_group.grosysid as source,
  pg_user.usesysid::varchar || '_' || pg_group.grosysid::varchar as id
FROM pg_group, pg_user 
WHERE pg_user.usesysid = ANY(pg_group.grolist) 
;

panels.title: Group assigned to User

targets.rawSQL: select current_database();

select
  database_type,
  database_name,
  database_owner
from SVV_REDSHIFT_DATABASES
order by 1, 2
;

select
  database_name as database,
  schema_type,
  schema_name,
  schema_owner,
  source_database,
  schema_option
from SVV_ALL_SCHEMAS
where database_name = current_database()
and schema_name not in ('pg_catalog', 'information_schema')
order by 1, 2
;

select
    database_name, 
    schema_name as schema, 
    table_type as relation_type,
    table_name as relation_name
from SVV_ALL_TABLES
where schema_name not in ('pg_catalog', 'information_schema')
and database_name = current_database()
order by 1, 2, 3, 4
;

select 
  database_name,
  schema_name,
  function_type,
  function_name,
  argument_type,
  result_type
from SVV_REDSHIFT_FUNCTIONS
where schema_name not in ('pg_catalog', 'information_schema')
and database_name = current_database()
order by 1, 2, 3, 4, 5, 6
;

panels.description: List of ML Model.

targets.rawSQL:
select
  current_database()::varchar as database_name,
	schema_name,
  model_name,
  model_state
  user_name,
  life_cycle,
  is_refreshable
from stv_ml_model_info
order by 1, 2, 3
;

panels.title: ML Model

panels.description: List of datashares. managed_by specifies the AWS service that manages the datashare.

targets.rawSQL:
select
  share_type, 
  share_name, 
  pg_user.usename as share_owner,
  producer_account, 
  producer_namespace, 
  source_database, 
  consumer_database, 
  is_publicaccessible, 
  createdate::varchar, 
  managed_by
from SVV_DATASHARES
left join pg_user
on pg_user.usesysid = share_owner
order by 1, 2
;

panels.title: Datashare
